modules.description: Handles TCP connections with customizable protocol processing, supporting both standard and upgradable connection flows. Operates on socket and address types to manage incoming network requests. Used to implement HTTP servers with protocol-specific request parsing and response generation.

Provides functions to initialize a connection with a specified buffer size and protocol, upgrade the connection to a different implementation, gracefully shut down the connection, and check if the connection is closed. Works with a custom connection type and socket type. Used to manage network communication in a non-blocking manner, such as handling WebSocket upgrades or controlling connection lifecycles in real-time applications.

Provides HTTP/2 protocol parsing and serialization using Angstrom and Faraday, handling frames, streams, and connection management. Works with byte sequences, headers, and stream identifiers to enable bidirectional communication. Used to build compliant HTTP/2 servers and clients within OCaml applications.

Handles HTTP/2 connection setup by creating a handler that processes incoming requests and errors, using a specified configuration. Operates on socket and address types to manage network communication. Used to establish and manage server-side HTTP/2 connections with custom request and error handling logic.
